Runtime secrets and the VPN user database are stored in this directory.
Do not publish it or include it in bug reports.
Per-user access policies are stored in /etc/config/ikev2-manager separately
from credentials. They follow the authenticated EAP identity even when the
inbound pool assigns a different virtual IPv4 address. Optional public_ports
entries expose only those TCP/UDP router ports to the matching active user.
When managed DNS is enabled, the original dnsproxy and dnsmasq UCI exports are
stored under dns-original/ so the previous resolver can be restored safely.
